				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard Tanks<a name="19438"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 5 04 6:41 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I find myself to be in this situation as I'm sure many other bards have in the past or still do.
<br />

<br />
We have WAY too many stats to try and max out in order to be the &quot;perfect&quot; bard we want to be.  The best thing to do I would say is to just enjoy playing the songs and play the songs you know that will make your group most beneficial.
<br />

<br />
We are severely hindered in dps due to no double attack, but we get AAs to help us get better.  The stats will come, but dps is mainly based off of skill and str, but also atk from items like vengence and auras and spells from rangers and SKs.
<br />

<br />
If you're playing your melee and spell dmg songs as you should, you won't need to worry about your dps, for you are making the other melees and casters better at theirs.
<br />

<br />
I wouldn't worry about putting any points into AA stats.  Of the 50+ magelo profiles I've looked at, very very few have put any points into stats. It's all about skills and utility for a bard.
<br />

<br />
Enjoy  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
