				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard Tanks<a name="19562"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 6 04 11:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree. Throughout my progression I've had spurts where I stood around more than meleed but I find myself always in the fray now unless we're raiding, in which case I might just be using my drums for the instrument boost. Ever played a druid past 55? We get this cute little pet bear thats COMPLETELY useless in combat, but when I play my druid I always have him out, because he can deter attackers and give me time to root or succor, and he's also a very small mana free Dot when I give him 2 weps and haste him with my necklace. Playing my bard is not comparable I know, but I thought I'd bring it up to make the point that every bit helps and being part of a team means you have to contribute everything you can at all times. Personally I chose gear to max out my str and I always use BDMG and Troub's Mace or Swiftblade of Zek. With chanty haste and overhaste Im FAST, and that's enough for me really, I think I do pretty good for a bard but I would never complain about it. I don't even have to tell you where our real strength is. 
<br />
    On a side note, because I don't really care about my melee damage I like to play around a lot with my weps, I have 3 backpacks in my bank full of other weps I switch in and out to play with, most of them are from the extra LDoN points I have and stuff I've gotten in trade from people (love trading). The good thing about this is that I have all my wep skills maxed all the time, the bad thing about it is that I always forget which ones I had on when I logged out and I'm always running to the bank to switch for raids and stuff, I can never decide which ones to keep with me and which ones to bank <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-10.gif" border="0" alt="Blushing" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
But whatever I have fun <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /></span></td>
